Class ParseTree

java.lang.Object
  edu.udel.trnka.pta.ParseTree
Direct Known Subclasses:
ComparedParseTree
public class ParseTree
extends java.lang.Object

Represents a single parse tree. Does not represent the rendering in any way; only the data.

Author:
keith.trnka

build

public static ParseTree build(java.lang.String s)
                       throws java.lang.Exception
builds a parse tree from the specified string. This checks to see whether the string is XML or labeled bracketing by checking the first non-whitespace character. If it's a '(', then labeled bracketing is used. Otherwise, XML is used.
